The paper deals with image set classification, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using a Riemannian kernel to determine similarities between sub-image sets, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions using benchmark datasets to test the proposed method, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE).
